es.ull.isaatc.simulation.sequential
Class WorkThread

java.lang.Object
  es.ull.isaatc.simulation.sequential.WorkThread
All Implemented Interfaces:
Identifiable, Prioritizable, java.lang.Comparable<WorkThread>
public class WorkThread
extends java.lang.Object
implements Identifiable, Prioritizable, java.lang.Comparable<WorkThread>

A sequential branch of activities in an element's flow. Represents an element instance, so multiple instances can be active at the same time.

There are three types of Work threads which require a different method to be created:

  1. Main thread. Is the element's main thread. Must be created by invoking the static method WorkThread.getInstanceMainWorkThread
  2. Descendant thread
    3. A thread created to carry out the inner flows of a structured flow. To invoke, use: getInstanceDescendantWorkThread
  3. Subsequent thread
    4. A thread created to carry out a new flow after a split. To invoke, use: getInstanceSubsequentWorkThread

A work thread has an associated token, which can be true or false. A false token is used only for synchronization purposes and doesn't execute task flows.

Author:
Iván Castilla Rodríguez
